analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: Market equilibrium hinges on liquidity stability amid rising volatility. With GMS at 52, the regime signifies a delicate transition where credit spread compression meets escalating VIX tail-risk. Despite idiosyncratic strength in semiconductor narratives, stagnant net liquidity and diverging global equity performance underscore a degradation in market breadth. Investors must navigate the fiscal-monetary nexus with vigilance as real interest rates sustain pressure on risk-asset valuations. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
